PERMISSION TO USE
  You may install and use official Mutualzz Bridge / Mutualzz Voice builds
  solely to connect Minecraft servers and clients to Mutualzz's hosted
  services, in accordance with Mutualzz's terms of service.

SOURCE VIEWING & CONTRIBUTIONS
  Source code may be made available for transparency, personal review, and
  community contributions.

  You may fork this repository and submit pull requests / patches back to
  Mutualzz. By submitting a contribution, you grant Mutualzz a perpetual,
  worldwide, royalty-free, irrevocable license to use, modify, and
  distribute your contribution as part of Mutualzz products under this
  license (or any Mutualzz license Mutualzz chooses for the project).

  Temporary forks used only to develop and propose contributions are allowed.
  Public forks must not be presented as official Mutualzz releases, and must
  not redistribute built jars for general use.

CONTRIBUTOR CREDIT
  Mutualzz will credit contributors for merged work. Credit is typically
  given through git history (author name and email on commits), GitHub pull
  request attribution, and release notes or changelogs when practical.
  Contributors remain free to list Mutualzz contributions in their own
  portfolios and résumés. Granting Mutualzz a license to your contribution
  does not waive credit or misattribute your work as solely Mutualzz-
  authored when credit is reasonably due.

PROHIBITED WITHOUT PRIOR WRITTEN PERMISSION FROM MUTUALZZ
  - Redistributing this software or modified versions as general-purpose
    downloads (jars, installers, or "unofficial builds")
  - Publishing builds to Modrinth, CurseForge, GitHub Releases, or similar
    for others to install
  - Operating or offering a third-party Mutualzz-compatible hub / bridge
    service using this software
  - Removing or altering copyright, license, or branding notices

MODIFICATIONS
  Personal, private modifications for your own Minecraft client or server are
  allowed only when used with Mutualzz's official hub. You may not distribute
  those modifications except by contributing them upstream to Mutualzz.

COMMERCIAL USE
  Commercial Minecraft servers may use official builds with a valid Mutualzz
  bridge token. Resale or bundling of this software requires a separate
  written agreement.

